BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Weekend: Kick Off Event\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260410T173000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260410T190000
UID:b72053411c12a8affd259bb5caa2680f@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:We are happy to promote the lovely MyPath trail which will one
  day bring walkers from Spencer to McCormick&rsquo\;s Creek State Park! Jo
 in Owen County Soil &amp\; Water at the trail head for an overview and the
 n a stroll along the path itself. Identify the flowers we see along the wa
 y as well as the tree planting area\, the Monarch Way Station\, the food f
 orest and more. Join us for this fun event! Meet: 788 Pottersville Road\, 
 Spencer. Owen County Soil &amp\; Water Conservation District Office
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Owen Co SWCD\, 788 Pottersville Ro
 ad\, Spencer\, 250 McCormick's Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Weekend: Native Plant Sale\, McCormick's Creek State Pa
 rk
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T093000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T120000
UID:03249103003e383b15c5440cff2f9c3a@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Every year some dedicated Friends members dig up lovely perenn
 ials from their yards and woods and donate them for this fundraising event
 . Plants will be available on a first-come\, first-serve basis. We will be
  happy to label and set your purchase aside to allow you to participate in
  the scheduled hikes and talks. Cash is preferred! Sale is happening at th
 e Nature Center.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Nature Center\, 250 McCormick's Cr
 eek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Weekend: Ecology of McCormick's Creek Cove Nature Prese
 rve\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T100000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T110000
UID:3d3c477605f5ab492cd8d4f575b7a9c7@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join Nature Preserves Community Ecologist`s\, Wyatt Williams\,
  to walk among towering oaks and hickories in this leisurely stroll throug
 h one of the park&#39\;s richest sites. Learn the names of the wildflowers
 \, but also how they fit into the system around them. This hike starts and
  ends at Friendly Shelter . This hike is rated moderate and is a .75-mile 
 round trip.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Friendly Shelter\, 250 McCormick's
  Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Weekend: Rugged Plants\, McCormick's Creek State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T140000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T150000
UID:abc64b5614d55f954902e3785889ce5c@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) Join David Mow\, Invasive Specialist and Master Gardene
 r Instructor\, at Centennial Shelter for a short hike on our new Echo Cany
 on Trail. You will discover how the acidic soil in this habitat and rock c
 liffs make it home to rare plants in the park.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, Centennial Shelter\, 250 McCormick
 's Creek Park Road\, Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Wildflower Weekend: Hike at the Bluff's\, McCormick's Creek State 
 Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T160000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260411T160000
UID:72c380c0569f61e6e00697f463b9e1d5@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:(Hike) oin State Ecologist\, Danielle Howard\, at Green Bluff&
 #39\;s Nature Preserve to learn what plants can live on the acidic steep c
 liff in Owen County. This hike is for advanced hikers only. We will be hik
 ing the North Loop Trail\, which is 1.2 miles\, on steep slopes\, and rugg
 ed terrain. Hiking poles are strongly suggested. Limited parking available
 . Meet: Green&#39\;s Bluff Nature Preserve-North Loop Spencer\, IN Trail D
 escription: The&nbsp\; North Loop Trail &nbsp\;is a 1.2-mile moderate loop
  trail through the northern section of Green&rsquo\;s Bluff. The gravel pa
 rking area at the trailhead can accommodate 5 vehicles\, with room for a f
 ew more along the road next to the cemetery. The trail overlooks hemlock b
 luffs above Raccoon Creek\, then descends a steep slope to continue along 
 the face of the bluff down to the creek. This portion of the trail can be 
 quite rugged. The trail continues along the creek\, where a sharp eye may 
 notice the stone foundation of James Green&rsquo\;s grist mill from the la
 te 1800s.
LOCATION:McCormick's Creek State Park\, 250 McCormick's Creek Park Road\, 
 Spencer\, IN 47460
URL:on.in.gov/mccormickscreek
X-SOURCE:McCormick's Creek State Park
END:VEVENT
